Package org.bonitasoft.engine.api

Interface ProfileAPI

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ProfileAPI
    public interface ProfileAPI
    Profiles are a notion used in Bonita Portal to give and control access to some specific features of the Bonita suite. Profiles are associated to Bonita Identity / Organization notions: users, groups, roles, memberships. ProfileAPI gives access to some of the profile administration: adding / removing members to / from a profile, retrieving / searching for profiles.
    Full control on profiles is part of Subscription editions of Bonita suite.
    Author:
    Celine Souchet, Matthieu Chaffotte
    See Also:
    SearchResult for general knowledege on Search mechanism in Bonita.

      • getNumberOfProfileMembers

        Map<Long,​Long> getNumberOfProfileMembers​(List<Long> profileIds)
        Retrieves the number of profile members for the profiles. The map contains the couples profileId/numberOfProfileMembers.

        If a profile does not exist, no exception is thrown and no value is added in the map.

        Parameters:
        profileIds - The identifiers of the profiles
        Returns:
        the number of profile members for the profiles
        Throws:
        RetrieveException - If an exception occurs during the profile retrieving
        InvalidSessionException - If the session is invalid (expired, unknown, ...)
        Since:
        6.0
